<p class="mt-4 mb-4">
  Being a man of quality, Adam arrived at Noc Noc at a punctual 5:45pm. After
  sitting in the bar alone for a bit, Adam thought it was odd that he hadn't
  heard from or seen Helen yet...
</p>

<p class="mt-4 mb-4">
  Meanwhile, across town, Helen was lost pedaling her way up San
  Francisco's notorious hills in an unfamiliar part of the city. Due to her
  lack of navigational excellence (<i>a trait she would come to deeply
  appreciate in her life partner</i>), Helen had fallen significantly behind
  Google Maps' predicted arrival time.
</p>

<p class="mt-4 mb-4">
  However, Adam didn't know any of this and was sitting alone in a bar with
  nothing but his thought &mdash; contemplating whether or not Helen was going to
  show up. Unsure what to do, he sent a quick messsage.
</p>

<.conversation messages={
  build_conversation([
    %{adam?: true, indicator?: true, text: "Hey everything ok?"}
  ])
} />

<p class="mt-4 mb-4">
  No response. So, approximately 15 minutes past the hour, Adam thought
  <i>well I guess the girl from the "cool startup" isn't showing up. It was a
    long shot anyway, time to go home.</i>
  He stood up to leave. As he was striding out,
  Adam spotted a vaguely familiar blonde walking with a bicycle;
  "Helen?" he queried.
</p>

<p class="mt-4 mb-4">
  "Adam?" Helen responded "Were you leaving?"
</p>

<p class="mt-4 mb-4">
  "Can I help you with your bike? How was your day?" Adam asked as he gave his
  most charming smile, hoping to smooth over the that he was leaving.
</p>
<p>
  "It was good but I got lost on the way over!" said Helen, who was immediately
  impressed with his bright smile. Adam then helped Helen guide her bike into a
  safe corner of the quiet bar, they ordered a drink, and the rest
  <.link
    target="_blank"
    class="text-blue-500 hover:underline hover:text-blue-600"
    href="https://travel.adamcollins.io"
  >
    is history...
  </.link>
</p>

<p class="mt-4 mb-4">
  Over the coming years Helen and Adam's love would grow with every adventure.
  Whether it was making skiing at Kirkwood,
  traveling across Asia, or playing video games in their beloved San Francisco
  apartment, there were most happy and fully themselves in each other's company.
  In the coming years they'd come to create some of the best memories
  of their young lives as they prepared to move to Chicago and start the next
  chapter; together.
</p>

